  m_Name: Extensor_digitorum_digitalis_lateralis_muscle.R
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Extensor_digitorum_digitalis_lateralis_muscle.R
  partName: Extensor digitorum digitalis lateralis muscle Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right extensor digitorum lateralis muscle occupies the lateral region of
    the canine forearm and functions primarily to extend the outer digits of the
    paw. It originates from the humerus and extends distally toward the phalanges,
    enabling controlled toe extension during locomotion.
  - This muscle contributes to balanced paw placement, coordination, and forelimb
    stability while walking, running, or changing direction. By assisting with digital
    extension, it helps maintain proper limb mechanics and prevents abnormal paw
    posture during movement. The muscle operates in conjunction with neighboring
    extensors to support smooth gait patterns.
